# VPS Key Manager

> Electron desktop app for authenticating with [vps-manager](https://github.com/Jok-Holk/vps-manager). Generates Ed25519 keypairs, signs server challenges, and issues one-time login credentials.

![Platform](https://img.shields.io/badge/platform-Windows%20%7C%20macOS%20%7C%20Linux-blue) ![Electron](https://img.shields.io/badge/electron-forge-teal)

---

## How it works

This app holds your **Ed25519 private key**, encrypted with OS-level storage (Windows DPAPI / macOS Keychain / libsecret on Linux). The private key never leaves your machine.

```
1. Open this app → enter your vps-manager URL
2. Click "Generate Credentials"
3. App signs a nonce from the server → server returns one-time key+pass
4. Copy key+pass → paste into vps-manager login page
5. Credentials expire in 10 minutes
```

The server only stores your **public key** (`PUBLIC_KEY_ED25519` in Settings). Even if the server is compromised, the private key is safe on your machine.

---

## Setup

### 1. Install

Download the latest release for your platform from [Releases](https://github.com/Jok-Holk/vps-key-manager/releases).

Or build from source:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Jok-Holk/vps-key-manager.git
cd vps-key-manager
npm install
npm run make
```

### 2. Configure server URL

Open the app → enter your vps-manager URL (e.g. `https://console.your-domain.com`) → click **Save**.

### 3. Generate keypair

Click **Generate Keypair** (first run only). This creates an Ed25519 keypair and stores the private key in OS-encrypted storage.

### 4. Register public key on server

The app shows your public key after generation (or click **Show Key** anytime).

Copy it → paste into vps-manager **Settings → Ed25519 Public Key** → Save.

If vps-manager is in first-run setup mode, log in with the setup password from PM2 logs first.

### 5. Login

Click **Generate Credentials** → copy the KEY and PASS → paste into vps-manager login page.

---

## Transfer to another machine

Your keypair is tied to the machine. To use the same key on another computer:

1. Enter the same **transfer password** on both machines
2. Source machine: click **↑ Export .vpskey** → save the file
3. Target machine: click **↓ Import .vpskey** → select the file, enter same password

The `.vpskey` file is encrypted with AES-256-GCM. The password is never stored.

---

## First-run flow with vps-manager

```
New VPS install
    ↓
vps-manager starts → prints SETUP PASSWORD in PM2 logs
    ↓
Browser → vps-manager login → enter setup password
    ↓
Open this app → Generate Keypair → copy public key
    ↓
vps-manager Settings → paste PUBLIC_KEY_ED25519 → Save
    ↓
Setup password disabled automatically
    ↓
From now on: use this app to generate login credentials
```

---

## Security

- Private key encrypted with OS keychain (DPAPI on Windows, Keychain on macOS)
- `.vpskey` export encrypted with AES-256-GCM + scrypt key derivation
- Private key never transmitted — only signatures
- One-time credentials expire in 10 minutes
- Server verifies Ed25519 signature before issuing credentials

---

## Build

```bash
# Development
npm start

# Package (current platform)
npm run make

# Package all platforms
npm run make -- --platform=win32,darwin,linux
```

Output in `out/` directory.

